DESCRIPTION:THIS PROJECT AIMS TO ESTABLISH AND BUILD ENVIRONMENTAL PROGRAM CAPACITY OF THREE INDIAN NATIONS: ONONDAGA NATION, TONAWANDA BAND OF SENECA, AND TUSCARORA NATION, WHO ARE THE MEMBER NATIONS OF AN INTERTRIBAL CONSORTIUM CALLED THE HAUDENOSAUNEE ENVIRONMENTAL TASK FORCE (HETF). THE PROJECT PURPOSE IS TO INCREASE THE CAPACITY OF THESE THREE INDIAN NATIONS TO DEVELOP THE NECESSARY ENVIRONMENTAL PROGRAMS ON NATION LANDS, AND IS DESIGNED TO LEAD TO ENVIRONMENTAL IMPROVEMENTS ON INDIAN NATION LAND THROUGH ENVIRONMENTAL ASSESSMENT AND DEVELOPMENT OF PROGRAMS IN THE AREAS OF CLIMATE CHANGE, WATER QUALITY, AIR QUALITY, SOLID WASTE, EMERGENCY RESPONSE, PESTICIDES, WETLANDS, AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH.ACTIVITIES:THE ACTIVITIES TO BE PERFORMED INCLUDE THE DEVELOPMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL PROGRAMS TO IMPROVE THE ENVIRONMENT ON INDIAN NATION LAND IN THE AREAS OF ENVIRONMENTAL ASSESSMENT, CLIMATE CHANGE, WATER QUALITY (DRINKING WATER AND/OR SURFACE WATER), AIR QUALITY, SOLID WASTE, EMERGENCY RESPONSE, PESTICIDES, WETLANDS, AND COMMUNITY OUTREACH:
-AN INCREASE IN CAPACITY THRU TRAINING AND WORKING WITH CONSULTANTS TO MONITOR AND IMPROVE OPEN DUMPING, SOLID WASTE, OR HOUSEHOLD HAZARDOUS WASTE; 
-AN INCREASE IN CAPACITY TO ASSESS AIR RESOURCES AND TO PERFORM EMISSIONS INVENTORY;
-ADDRESSING CLIMATE CHANGE AND ITS IMPACT TO HAUDENOSAUNEE HEALTH AND CULTURE;
-HOLDING ROADSIDE CLEANUP DAYS, LARGE ITEM COLLECTION EVENTS, HAZARDOUS WASTE COLLECTION DAYS, AND ADDRESSING OPEN DUMPING
-INCREASING RECYCLING CAPABILITIES AND IMPROVING RECYCLING THROUGHOUT EACH COMMUNITY
-CONTINUE TO ENHANCE STEWARDSHIP OF NATION LANDS AND RESOURCES IN ORDER TO CONSERVE AND IMPROVE THE HEALTH AND VALUE OF SUCH RESOURCES FOR CURRENT AND FUTURE GENERATIONS.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:THE ANTICIPATED DELIVERABLES AND EXPECTED OUTCOMES WILL BE REPORTED TO EPA ON AN ANNUAL BASIS AT PROGRAM REVIEW MEETINGS OR VIA TELECONFERENCE OR VIRTUAL MEETINGS. SOME ANTICIPATED DELIVERABLES AND EXPECTED OUTCOMES INCLUDE:
-AN INCREASE IN CAPACITY OF EACH NATION TO MONITOR AND IMPROVE OPEN DUMPING, SOLID WASTE, OR HOUSEHOLD HAZARDOUS WASTE; 
-AN INCREASE IN CAPACITY TO ASSESS AIR RESOURCES AND TO PERFORM EMISSIONS INVENTORY;
-ADDRESSING CLIMATE CHANGE AND ITS IMPACT TO HAUDENOSAUNEE HEALTH AND CULTURE;
-EACH NATION WILL HOLD ROADSIDE CLEANUP DAYS, LARGE ITEM COLLECTION EVENTS, HAZARDOUS WASTE COLLECTION DAYS, AND ADDRESSING OPEN DUMPING
-INCREASE RECYCLING CAPABILITIES AND IN TURN IMPROVE RECYCLING THROUGHOUT EACH COMMUNITY
-EFFORTS TO CONTINUE AND ENHANCE STEWARDSHIP OF NATION LANDS AND RESOURCES IN ORDER TO CONSERVE AND IMPROVE THE HEALTH AND VALUE OF SUCH RESOURCES FOR CURRENT AND FUTURE GENERATIONS. 
-THE INTENDED BENEFICIARIES ARE THE CITIZENS OF THE ONONDAGA NATION, TONAWANDA SENECA NATION, AND TUSCARORA NATION.

DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT PROVIDES ASSISTANCE TO THE PUEBLO OF SAN ILDEFONSO TO BUILD ITS CAPACITY TO ADMINISTER ENVIRONMENTAL PROGRAMS ON INDIAN LANDS. SPECIFICALLY, DECP CURRENTLY CONSISTS OF EIGHT STAFF MEMBERS (FIVE OF WHOM ARE SAN ILDEFONSO PUEBLO
MEMBERS), EACH WITH SPECIALIZED RESPONSIBILITIES ADDRESSING SUCH ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES AS:
- QUALITY OF SURFACE AND GROUND WATER RESOURCES;
- ENSURING DRINKING WATER QUALITY;
- EXISTING RADIOACTIVE AND HAZARDOUS MATERIALS CONTAMINATION;
- ACUTE AND CUMULATIVE HUMAN HEALTH RISKS DUE TO PAST AND ONGOING CONTAMINATION;
- IMPACTS TO LOCAL AND REGIONAL AIR QUALITY;
- EFFECTS OF ILLEGAL DUMPING, AND UPDATING OF THE TRIBES SOLID WASTE MANAGEMENT PLAN;
- BIOACCUMULATION AND UPTAKE OF RADIOACTIVE AND OTHER HARMFUL SUBSTANCES BY BIOTA AND OTHER
RESOURCES WITH TRADITIONAL CULTURAL SIGNIFICANCE;
- COORDINATION OF GIS/GPS MAPPING IN SUPPORT OF ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING AND
SURVEILLANCE PROJECTS;
- TRIBAL RISK ASSESSMENT, RISK MANAGEMENT, AND RISK COMMUNICATION;
- DATABASE DEVELOPMENT AND MAINTENANCE;
- UNDERGROUND STORAGE TANKS.

ACTIVITIES:SPECIFICALLY, THE RECIPIENT WILL BUILD CAPACITY OF OFFICE STAFF TO LEARN AND ADDRESS ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES, PROVIDE OUTREACH, IMPLEMENT SOLID WASTE MANAGEMENT PRACTICES AND STRATEGIES TO PREVENT ILLEGAL DUMPING, AND CAPACITY DEVELOPMENT FOR DRINKING WATER SYSTEM.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:QUARTERLY PROGRESS REPORTS, ANNUAL FINAL FINANCIAL REPORT ( FFR), QUALITY MANAGEMENT PLAN (QMP), GEOGRAPHIC INFORMATION SYSTEM/GLOBAL POSITIONING SYSTEM (GIS/GPS); QUALITY ASSURANCE PERFORMANCE PLAN (QAPP), ETEP UPDATE. 
THE PUEBLO OF SAN ILDEFONSO IS THE INTENDED BENEFICIARY.
